1
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:08,960
Wanneung I’m gonna be a superstar,
just like everyone else!

2
00:00:08,960 --> 00:00:11,680
Win Pawee actually agreed to do the movie?

3
00:00:11,920 --> 00:00:13,720
Congratulations!

4
00:00:13,720 --> 00:00:15,320
I’ve got a gift for you.

5
00:00:16,400 --> 00:00:17,720
A cactus?

6
00:00:17,720 --> 00:00:19,480
I’ll put my name on the line

7
00:00:19,480 --> 00:00:20,600
… she can do it.

8
00:00:20,600 --> 00:00:22,240
And she’s perfect for this role.

9
00:00:22,280 --> 00:00:24,080
You’re a star now, Wanneung.

10
00:00:24,240 --> 00:00:25,680
Congrats.

11
00:00:25,680 --> 00:00:28,000
You don’t notice anything?

12
00:00:28,600 --> 00:00:30,040
Did you redecorate?

13
00:00:30,080 --> 00:00:31,760
Are you mad at me?

14
00:00:31,800 --> 00:00:33,280
I’ve got good news.

15
00:00:33,320 --> 00:00:35,000
Come out and hear it, please.

16
00:00:36,200 --> 00:00:37,200
Wanneung.

17
00:00:38,480 --> 00:00:40,560
You signed with P’ Waanwaan?

18
00:00:40,640 --> 00:00:43,000
Yeah. You’re happy for me, right?

19
00:00:43,040 --> 00:00:46,920
I signed with the number one talent manager!

20
00:00:48,320 --> 00:00:49,960
Look into my eyes.

21
00:00:50,040 --> 00:00:51,720
See if I look happy.

22
00:00:51,760 --> 00:00:53,480
And here’s what I want to tell you.

23
00:00:59,560 --> 00:01:00,880
You were about to say

24
00:01:00,920 --> 00:01:03,320
you’re happy I’m about to make it,

25
00:01:03,360 --> 00:01:06,120
and you’ll stay by my side forever.

26
00:01:06,240 --> 00:01:09,360
And you wanted to tell me...

27
00:01:10,360 --> 00:01:11,920
that you like me,

28
00:01:11,960 --> 00:01:13,280
right?

29
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:28,840
So, Wanneung?

30
00:01:30,720 --> 00:01:33,240
You’re happy for me, right?

31
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:35,120
Happy? For what?

32
00:01:36,280 --> 00:01:37,280
Win…

33
00:01:37,720 --> 00:01:39,000
Win.

34
00:01:40,320 --> 00:01:43,040
Are you mad I signed without asking you?

35
00:01:43,280 --> 00:01:45,280
I really did try calling you.

36
00:01:45,320 --> 00:01:47,320
But you never picked up.

37
00:01:48,560 --> 00:01:50,240
Why would I be mad?

38
00:01:50,480 --> 00:01:52,400
It’s your life. Do what you want.

39
00:01:53,120 --> 00:01:54,840
We’re not anything anyway.

40
00:01:56,280 --> 00:01:57,280
It’s just...

41
00:01:57,560 --> 00:01:59,840
I saw P’ Waanwaan used to manage you,

42
00:01:59,960 --> 00:02:02,680
so I trusted her and signed with her.

43
00:02:05,080 --> 00:02:07,680
Don’t you know how ruthless she is?

44
00:02:08,040 --> 00:02:09,880
What she did to me?

45
00:02:11,600 --> 00:02:13,960
What did P’ Waanwaan do to you?

46
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:15,800
Tell me.

47
00:02:15,880 --> 00:02:17,800
What happened to you?

48
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:28,760
That’s my “Echinopsis calochlora.”

49
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:31,120
That’s my cactus!

50
00:02:31,920 --> 00:02:33,680
It’s something I really love.

51
00:02:33,720 --> 00:02:36,280
Why would you do this to it?

52
00:02:39,120 --> 00:02:40,880
Oh, my poor baby.

53
00:02:41,480 --> 00:02:43,760
You were born a cactus…

54
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,240
no leaves at all,

55
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:47,040
so tough and resilient,

56
00:02:47,040 --> 00:02:49,920
and now you have to die this young?

57
00:02:50,960 --> 00:02:52,240
You’re so cruel.

58
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:55,160
Being cruel to me wasn’t enough,
now you’re cruel to my plant too?

59
00:02:55,560 --> 00:02:58,320
Do you know how much I love it?

60
00:03:00,160 --> 00:03:02,000
It’s not dead.

61
00:03:02,040 --> 00:03:04,480
Just replant it and change the pot.

62
00:03:04,840 --> 00:03:06,440
It’s not the same.

63
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:09,280
These pots are its home.

64
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:12,120
I’ve taken such good care of it.

65
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:13,920
It means so much to me.

66
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:16,240
That pot is one of a kind.

67
00:03:17,040 --> 00:03:18,480
I didn’t mean to.

68
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:20,720
Can you not make a big deal out of this?

69
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:28,360
Let me see.

70
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:32,720
Didn’t anyone teach you
ceramic can cut?

71
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:36,760
I’m stupid.

72
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:38,200
Happy now?

73
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:40,160
Wait.

74
00:04:15,440 --> 00:04:17,920
Don’t you notice anything?

75
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:28,800
Did you redecorate?

76
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:31,360
Right?

77
00:05:59,280 --> 00:06:01,040
Wanneung, you idiot.

78
00:06:01,080 --> 00:06:03,200
I’m seriously too chill.

79
00:09:02,480 --> 00:09:03,560
All done.

80
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:07,440
Thanks so much, Tom,
for bringing this over so early.

81
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:10,360
Are you sure you don’t want me to go with you?

82
00:09:10,840 --> 00:09:13,520
It’s okay. I know you’re busy.

83
00:09:13,640 --> 00:09:16,520
Between the café and filming the series.

84
00:09:16,640 --> 00:09:19,360
Travel safe.

85
00:09:20,800 --> 00:09:23,760
Thank you. And please don’t forget about that.

86
00:09:24,800 --> 00:09:25,800
Okay.

87
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:28,120
Tom.

88
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:30,920
Hi. What are you doing here so early?

89
00:09:30,920 --> 00:09:32,480
Just dropping something off for her.

90
00:09:35,880 --> 00:09:37,160
I’ll get going.

91
00:10:01,160 --> 00:10:02,320
Go pack your bags.

92
00:10:12,440 --> 00:10:13,920
Why are you crying?

93
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:16,200
Win…

94
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:17,840
I know I messed up.

95
00:10:17,880 --> 00:10:20,160
I know I didn’t listen to you, but...

96
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:22,680
Are you really kicking me out?

97
00:10:22,720 --> 00:10:24,800
Why are you being so cruel?

98
00:10:25,440 --> 00:10:27,680
You even drew a line in the house.

99
00:10:27,880 --> 00:10:28,880
Is it because...

100
00:10:29,160 --> 00:10:31,800
you don’t want me living here anymore?

101
00:10:33,560 --> 00:10:35,600
I’m sorry.

102
00:10:35,640 --> 00:10:37,800
I was wrong.

103
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:41,880
Stop crying first.

104
00:10:45,480 --> 00:10:46,800
Just stop crying.

105
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:48,440
Calm down, okay?

106
00:10:50,280 --> 00:10:51,600
Stop crying.

107
00:10:52,920 --> 00:10:54,440
And follow me.

108
00:11:03,520 --> 00:11:05,840
Your “Echinopsis calochlora” cactus.

109
00:11:11,120 --> 00:11:13,680
I stayed up all night

110
00:11:13,920 --> 00:11:15,320
putting it back together.

111
00:11:26,880 --> 00:11:28,720
Sorry I broke it.

112
00:11:35,760 --> 00:11:37,120
Win…

113
00:11:43,360 --> 00:11:46,440
About the contract you
signed with P’ Waanwaan,

114
00:11:46,920 --> 00:11:49,080
I had Tom send it to a lawyer to review,

115
00:11:49,160 --> 00:11:51,000
in case there’s anything unfair to you.

116
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:53,480
But I already signed it.

117
00:11:53,520 --> 00:11:55,200
Can we even fix anything?

118
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:59,760
At least we’ll know and be more careful.

119
00:12:04,320 --> 00:12:05,760
Win…

120
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:08,920
I thought you were going to hate me.

121
00:12:09,280 --> 00:12:12,480
Do you know
I couldn’t sleep at all last night?

122
00:12:12,560 --> 00:12:14,960
I even cooked to make it up to you,

123
00:12:14,960 --> 00:12:17,520
but you wouldn’t come out to eat.

124
00:12:19,720 --> 00:12:22,320
I was putting your pot back together.

125
00:12:22,960 --> 00:12:24,720
Why are you crying?

126
00:12:32,040 --> 00:12:34,360
Why are you crying?

127
00:12:34,800 --> 00:12:36,600
Is it because I didn’t fix it nicely?

128
00:12:41,960 --> 00:12:45,040
You’re so kind to me.

129
00:12:46,040 --> 00:12:49,440
No one’s ever been this kind to me before.

130
00:12:49,680 --> 00:12:52,520
I don’t even know how to thank you.

131
00:12:58,000 --> 00:12:59,280
Then...

132
00:13:00,120 --> 00:13:01,960
just be good and...

133
00:13:02,600 --> 00:13:04,320
listen to me. That’s enough.

134
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:05,600
Okay?

135
00:13:07,040 --> 00:13:10,000
From now on,
I’ll listen to you in everything, Win.

136
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:14,880
Go. Pack your bags.

137
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:18,440
Where are you sending me?

138
00:13:18,560 --> 00:13:20,200
I don’t have anywhere else to go.

139
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:23,280
Please let me stay here.

140
00:13:23,760 --> 00:13:25,440
I’m not kicking you out.

141
00:13:26,160 --> 00:13:28,800
Go pack your bags. Just bring...

142
00:13:28,880 --> 00:13:30,680
a few outfits. That’s enough.

143
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:37,840
Didn’t you say you’d listen to me?

144
00:14:18,480 --> 00:14:19,880
(Meedee)

145
00:14:21,240 --> 00:14:22,360
(Meedee)

146
00:14:32,640 --> 00:14:34,040
You and that woman…

147
00:14:34,560 --> 00:14:36,520
there’s nothing special between you, right?

148
00:14:38,080 --> 00:14:40,240
Why would you ask that?

149
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:43,920
It’s just... you seem especially
worried about her.

150
00:14:43,960 --> 00:14:45,560
So I just wanted to make sure.

151
00:14:48,040 --> 00:14:49,440
You know...

152
00:14:50,680 --> 00:14:52,480
I’m pretty scarred from love.

153
00:14:52,640 --> 00:14:54,360
I’m scared to open up again.

154
00:14:56,400 --> 00:14:57,760
But maybe...

155
00:14:58,840 --> 00:15:01,640
she could be the one
who makes you take that risk again.

156
00:15:06,960 --> 00:15:08,320
I want to know too

157
00:15:08,360 --> 00:15:10,280
if I can take that risk again.

158
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:26,680
Win.

159
00:16:20,040 --> 00:16:23,280
What a scam.
I thought this was a relaxing trip.

160
00:16:23,320 --> 00:16:27,360
Turns out we’re here to suffer.
If I’d known, I wouldn’t have come.

161
00:16:28,360 --> 00:16:29,680
What are you mumbling?

162
00:16:32,240 --> 00:16:37,640
Nothing. I’m not complaining
at all, Win Pawee.

163
00:16:38,520 --> 00:16:39,760
Okay.

164
00:16:42,080 --> 00:16:44,840
When you’re done there,
come help here too.

165
00:16:44,880 --> 00:16:46,480
Okay.

166
00:16:59,560 --> 00:17:01,040
You take that side.

167
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:15,160
Let’s pull at the same time.

168
00:17:15,280 --> 00:17:16,480
Okay.

169
00:17:16,640 --> 00:17:19,160
One, two, three.

170
00:17:24,920 --> 00:17:26,480
All done?

171
00:17:26,520 --> 00:17:27,560
All done.

172
00:17:40,840 --> 00:17:42,360
It’s so pretty.

173
00:17:44,040 --> 00:17:46,800
Right? So can you stop complaining now?

174
00:17:46,840 --> 00:17:49,120
I even brought you somewhere beautiful.

175
00:17:49,120 --> 00:17:51,960
It’s quiet and peaceful.
You’ll be able to focus.

176
00:17:52,360 --> 00:17:54,600
If you’re going to be an actress,

177
00:17:54,640 --> 00:17:56,760
you need concentration, you know?

178
00:17:58,520 --> 00:18:00,040
Don’t pretend you’re being nice.

179
00:18:00,080 --> 00:18:02,760
You wanted this trip but didn’t dare
sleep alone in a tent

180
00:18:02,760 --> 00:18:04,440
because you’re scared of ghosts, right?

181
00:18:08,120 --> 00:18:09,680
The weather’s so nice.

182
00:18:10,920 --> 00:18:12,080
Win…

183
00:18:12,880 --> 00:18:14,160
Where are you going?

184
00:18:14,920 --> 00:18:16,040
Win…

185
00:18:19,360 --> 00:18:20,560
Where are you going?

186
00:18:35,840 --> 00:18:37,440
You brought me here…

187
00:18:37,480 --> 00:18:40,040
Is there something you want to tell me, Win?

188
00:18:41,440 --> 00:18:43,600
Can I ask you something, Wanneung?

189
00:18:43,600 --> 00:18:44,680
Of course.

190
00:19:06,103 --> 00:19:07,383
The nurse is out.

191
00:19:07,543 --> 00:19:09,663
Excuse me, how is she?

192
00:19:09,663 --> 00:19:12,383
Please wait for the doctor’s statement.

193
00:19:24,503 --> 00:19:26,503
The test results are out now, right?

194
00:19:26,943 --> 00:19:28,583
Everything’s normal.

195
00:19:28,943 --> 00:19:31,343
- Then move the patient to a room.
- Yes, doctor.

196
00:19:31,383 --> 00:19:34,103
But there are reporters everywhere.

197
00:19:34,183 --> 00:19:37,543
Just tell them the truth,
that the patient is safe.

198
00:19:37,543 --> 00:19:40,103
- But don’t let them disturb her.
- Yes.

199
00:20:21,183 --> 00:20:22,183
Hey.

200
00:20:27,743 --> 00:20:28,863
Win…

201
00:20:29,543 --> 00:20:32,463
- What?
- How much farther are we walking?

202
00:20:32,743 --> 00:20:34,863
Just... taking it slow.

203
00:20:35,143 --> 00:20:36,503
The weather’s nice.

204
00:20:36,543 --> 00:20:38,303
The view’s nice too.

205
00:20:40,263 --> 00:20:41,463
You don’t like it?

206
00:20:42,423 --> 00:20:44,183
The weather’s great,
I won’t argue with that.

207
00:20:44,223 --> 00:20:47,663
But after walking this far,
I’m too tired to enjoy the view.

208
00:20:54,663 --> 00:20:55,703
Let’s go.

209
00:20:57,543 --> 00:20:59,783
You’re walking again?

210
00:21:25,943 --> 00:21:27,503
So pretty.

211
00:21:29,543 --> 00:21:31,383
So refreshing.

212
00:21:38,343 --> 00:21:39,383
Hey…

213
00:21:40,383 --> 00:21:41,383
You’re getting wet.

214
00:21:41,903 --> 00:21:44,663
Careful, the current’s strong.

215
00:21:45,263 --> 00:21:48,143
The weather’s nice,
so I wanted to play in the water.

216
00:21:48,183 --> 00:21:50,503
It’s cool and refreshing.

217
00:21:54,663 --> 00:21:57,263
You don’t get weather like this often.

218
00:21:57,263 --> 00:21:59,663
In Bangkok it’s just crowded buildings.

219
00:21:59,703 --> 00:22:01,943
The air’s bad, PM2.5 everywhere.

220
00:22:01,983 --> 00:22:05,343
But here, the air is so good.

221
00:22:05,383 --> 00:22:07,063
It’s so relaxing.

222
00:22:09,743 --> 00:22:11,183
Try it.

223
00:22:11,223 --> 00:22:13,983
Take a deep breath,
it really feels refreshing.

224
00:22:14,743 --> 00:22:16,663
Breathe in…

225
00:22:17,383 --> 00:22:18,423
together…

226
00:22:18,463 --> 00:22:21,903
- No thanks, I’m breathing just fine.
- Hey!

227
00:22:22,463 --> 00:22:24,143
That’s not the same.

228
00:22:24,183 --> 00:22:26,783
If you don’t fill your lungs,
they’ll get clogged.

229
00:22:29,783 --> 00:22:31,903
Who told you your lungs would get clogged?

230
00:22:32,583 --> 00:22:35,303
Try being more relaxed
with people sometimes.

231
00:22:36,063 --> 00:22:37,623
- Please?
- No.

232
00:22:37,943 --> 00:22:39,263
Please, please, please, please.

233
00:22:39,303 --> 00:22:40,903
Come on, spread your arms.

234
00:22:42,743 --> 00:22:43,983
Arms out.

235
00:22:44,023 --> 00:22:45,423
And breathe in.

236
00:22:45,423 --> 00:22:46,663
Breathe in.

237
00:22:46,703 --> 00:22:48,543
Breathe in.

238
00:22:48,583 --> 00:22:50,583
Arms out, breathe in.

239
00:22:51,663 --> 00:22:52,983
Hey…

240
00:22:52,983 --> 00:22:54,863
Am I really that annoying?

241
00:22:55,183 --> 00:22:57,143
I’ll go take pictures somewhere else.

242
00:23:05,743 --> 00:23:06,983
Win…

243
00:23:07,103 --> 00:23:08,983
When did you get over there?

244
00:23:10,623 --> 00:23:12,103
You were busy taking photos.

245
00:23:12,143 --> 00:23:13,983
Come on, come on.

246
00:23:16,663 --> 00:23:18,503
- It’s…
- Win…

247
00:23:18,503 --> 00:23:20,503
Be careful, the current’s strong.

248
00:23:20,703 --> 00:23:21,783
Okay?

249
00:23:21,943 --> 00:23:23,583
Let’s just take pictures.

250
00:23:24,383 --> 00:23:26,703
Then just take pictures of the view.

251
00:23:26,743 --> 00:23:28,183
Why include me?

252
00:23:28,183 --> 00:23:30,343
Because I want a photo with you.

253
00:23:30,343 --> 00:23:31,783
We came all the way here together.

254
00:23:31,983 --> 00:23:33,743
No, I don’t like taking pictures.

255
00:23:33,823 --> 00:23:36,263
Please? Come on, Win, please.

256
00:23:36,303 --> 00:23:37,863
Just one photo.

257
00:23:38,543 --> 00:23:40,463
One, two…

258
00:23:44,023 --> 00:23:45,343
So cute.

259
00:24:18,863 --> 00:24:20,183
How are you doing?

260
00:24:20,823 --> 00:24:23,183
My legs feel like they’re about to fall off.

261
00:24:24,343 --> 00:24:25,583
How about this…

262
00:24:26,023 --> 00:24:28,783
whoever gets to the lodge last

263
00:24:28,823 --> 00:24:30,503
has to treat the other to dinner.

264
00:24:30,543 --> 00:24:32,303
Win…

265
00:24:32,343 --> 00:24:35,263
- Win, Win!
- I’m almost there!

266
00:24:36,143 --> 00:24:38,183
I can’t do this anymore.

267
00:24:46,823 --> 00:24:48,063
I’m so sore.

268
00:24:48,103 --> 00:24:50,783
Hurry up, the sun’s about to set.

269
00:24:50,903 --> 00:24:51,983
Just a second.

270
00:24:52,023 --> 00:24:53,823
I’m really sore.

271
00:24:53,903 --> 00:24:56,223
We walked so much today.

272
00:24:56,263 --> 00:24:59,063
If you keep massaging like that,
it’ll get dark soon.

273
00:25:01,623 --> 00:25:03,983
Then you can go ahead without me.

274
00:25:04,023 --> 00:25:05,503
I’ll catch up.

275
00:25:05,503 --> 00:25:08,983
I know you don’t like the dark.

276
00:25:10,543 --> 00:25:14,503
We walked so much today, I’m so sore.

277
00:25:14,543 --> 00:25:17,903
I can’t do it anymore, I can’t walk.

278
00:25:20,303 --> 00:25:22,183
I’m so sore.

279
00:25:23,543 --> 00:25:24,583
Get on.

280
00:25:24,783 --> 00:25:25,943
Really?

281
00:25:28,103 --> 00:25:29,983
Hurry before I change my mind.

282
00:25:31,263 --> 00:25:32,463
Stay still.

283
00:25:33,903 --> 00:25:36,463
One, two, three.

284
00:25:36,503 --> 00:25:37,983
Three, three!

285
00:25:38,943 --> 00:25:41,103
You’re fast when it’s something like this.

286
00:25:42,423 --> 00:25:43,703
Thank you.

287
00:25:43,703 --> 00:25:46,383
No need. I just want to get back quickly.

288
00:25:47,303 --> 00:25:49,463
You’re such a softie.

289
00:25:59,103 --> 00:26:00,503
Did you fall asleep?

290
00:26:00,503 --> 00:26:03,183
It’s way too quiet back there.

291
00:26:04,623 --> 00:26:05,663
Today…

292
00:26:05,703 --> 00:26:07,023
was so much fun.

293
00:26:07,023 --> 00:26:10,303
I haven’t been on a trip like this in so long.

294
00:26:10,343 --> 00:26:12,703
Thank you for bringing me here.

295
00:26:14,983 --> 00:26:16,583
You brought me here…

296
00:26:16,623 --> 00:26:19,183
Is there something you want to tell me, Win?

297
00:26:19,903 --> 00:26:21,503
If there is, just say it.

298
00:26:21,503 --> 00:26:23,823
Don’t leave me overthinking by myself.

299
00:26:23,863 --> 00:26:26,463
I’m dying to know.

300
00:26:34,103 --> 00:26:35,103
Sorry.

301
00:26:39,823 --> 00:26:41,503
Are you feeling dizzy?

302
00:26:43,183 --> 00:26:44,383
A little.

303
00:26:45,383 --> 00:26:47,103
You hit your head.

304
00:26:47,463 --> 00:26:49,783
What do you remember about
what happened before that?

305
00:26:55,423 --> 00:26:56,503
Win.

306
00:26:59,903 --> 00:27:04,543
(Sawalak Missed Call)

307
00:27:07,543 --> 00:27:09,183
Did anyone come to see me?

308
00:27:09,783 --> 00:27:10,783
No.

309
00:27:10,823 --> 00:27:13,103
Just reporters. I sent them all away.

310
00:27:18,823 --> 00:27:20,903
So, do you know who I am now?

311
00:27:25,463 --> 00:27:26,783
I do.

312
00:27:28,023 --> 00:27:29,583
Next time, just tell me.

313
00:27:30,063 --> 00:27:32,183
How was I supposed to know you’re a star?

314
00:27:36,663 --> 00:27:38,783
Other than the headache,

315
00:27:38,983 --> 00:27:40,383
any other symptoms?

316
00:27:40,743 --> 00:27:41,743
Stomach pain.

317
00:27:42,623 --> 00:27:43,783
Chest tightness?

318
00:27:45,823 --> 00:27:47,463
Any trouble breathing?

319
00:27:48,103 --> 00:27:49,263
No.

320
00:27:53,743 --> 00:27:54,863
Thank you.

321
00:27:55,423 --> 00:27:57,783
At least there’s someone
who cares about me.

322
00:27:58,863 --> 00:28:00,543
Don’t forget, I’m a doctor.

323
00:28:00,943 --> 00:28:02,663
I’m just doing my job.

324
00:28:37,663 --> 00:28:41,543
Mirada Chudpithak

325
00:28:56,223 --> 00:28:57,743
Go on, try a bite.

326
00:28:57,783 --> 00:28:59,943
Win Pawee’s cooking…

327
00:28:59,943 --> 00:29:01,503
let’s see how good it is.

328
00:29:08,263 --> 00:29:09,383
Hey…

329
00:29:09,663 --> 00:29:12,183
Your cooking’s actually pretty good.

330
00:29:12,423 --> 00:29:13,783
Want to try?

331
00:29:17,063 --> 00:29:18,063
I’ll feed you.

332
00:29:29,063 --> 00:29:30,383
Nice.

333
00:29:37,023 --> 00:29:38,103
Win…

334
00:29:40,463 --> 00:29:43,263
You’re not mad at me anymore, right?

335
00:29:45,063 --> 00:29:46,383
Mad about what?

336
00:29:48,743 --> 00:29:49,903
Well…

337
00:29:50,143 --> 00:29:53,263
about me signing with P’ Waanwaan.

338
00:29:59,303 --> 00:30:00,783
At first, I was.

339
00:30:05,783 --> 00:30:09,463
But honestly, I was more annoyed at myself
for not answering your call that day.

340
00:30:09,503 --> 00:30:11,783
That’s why things escalated like this.

341
00:30:14,663 --> 00:30:17,223
But I get that this is your dream.

342
00:30:17,263 --> 00:30:19,063
And if this is your opportunity,

343
00:30:19,103 --> 00:30:20,783
I shouldn’t stand in your way.

344
00:30:28,623 --> 00:30:30,903
Can I ask you something, Wanneung?

345
00:30:32,023 --> 00:30:33,103
Of course.

346
00:30:37,303 --> 00:30:38,783
Promise me…

347
00:30:39,903 --> 00:30:41,183
no matter what

348
00:30:41,183 --> 00:30:42,943
P’ Waanwaan asks you to do,

349
00:30:42,943 --> 00:30:44,663
whatever it is,

350
00:30:45,103 --> 00:30:47,463
you’ll tell me everything.

351
00:30:49,063 --> 00:30:50,383
Of course.

352
00:30:50,383 --> 00:30:52,863
I promise I’ll tell you everything.

353
00:30:53,023 --> 00:30:54,183
Promise.

354
00:30:59,983 --> 00:31:01,263
I promise.

355
00:31:19,343 --> 00:31:20,583
Promise, okay?

356
00:31:21,383 --> 00:31:22,383
Okay.

357
00:31:23,583 --> 00:31:24,983
Promise.

358
00:32:01,063 --> 00:32:02,143
Wanneung.

359
00:32:02,943 --> 00:32:04,383
Are you asleep?

360
00:32:05,463 --> 00:32:07,583
I’m not asleep.

361
00:32:07,783 --> 00:32:11,103
I’m just a little tipsy from the beer.

362
00:32:11,543 --> 00:32:13,263
You drank beer?

363
00:32:15,103 --> 00:32:17,743
I saw you drinking,

364
00:32:17,743 --> 00:32:19,783
so I wanted to try too.

365
00:32:19,823 --> 00:32:22,783
It’s my first time ever.

366
00:32:22,783 --> 00:32:24,383
Was I good?

367
00:32:27,343 --> 00:32:28,583
Wanneung.

368
00:32:36,063 --> 00:32:37,903
You really do get into trouble.

369
00:33:16,903 --> 00:33:18,183
Win…

370
00:33:24,023 --> 00:33:25,463
My heart…

371
00:33:26,623 --> 00:33:28,383
it’s beating so fast.

372
00:33:33,463 --> 00:33:35,183
Let me listen.

373
00:33:51,863 --> 00:33:53,263
Are you scared?

374
00:33:55,983 --> 00:33:57,743
No.

375
00:33:58,703 --> 00:34:00,103
I’m…

376
00:34:01,223 --> 00:34:02,703
just excited.

377
00:34:09,263 --> 00:34:10,903
And if we do this…

378
00:34:11,903 --> 00:34:13,463
will it calm me down?

379
00:34:21,503 --> 00:34:23,903
Close your eyes and take a deep breath.

380
00:37:10,263 --> 00:37:11,103
Win.

381
00:37:11,103 --> 00:37:12,543
I can put it away myself.

382
00:37:12,543 --> 00:37:14,143
But I’m happy to be of service.

383
00:37:14,143 --> 00:37:15,063
Are you flirting with me?

384
00:37:15,063 --> 00:37:15,903
At this point,

385
00:37:15,903 --> 00:37:16,983
I don’t even need to try.

386
00:37:16,983 --> 00:37:20,263
Win, what are you talking about?

387
00:38:48,808 --> 00:38:49,808
Wanneung.

388
00:38:53,448 --> 00:38:55,328
We only stayed one night.

389
00:38:55,328 --> 00:38:57,288
We have to go back today.

390
00:38:59,808 --> 00:39:01,688
Why? You don’t want to leave?

391
00:39:03,288 --> 00:39:05,688
Whenever I come back from a trip,

392
00:39:05,688 --> 00:39:07,168
I always feel like

393
00:39:07,208 --> 00:39:09,728
I’m waking up from a dream to face reality.

394
00:39:09,728 --> 00:39:11,048
I hate that feeling.

395
00:39:11,088 --> 00:39:15,248
Because dreams and reality
are never the same.

396
00:39:18,368 --> 00:39:21,328
Once you become a famous actress,

397
00:39:21,568 --> 00:39:23,608
you might forget about today.

398
00:39:29,488 --> 00:39:30,848
How

399
00:39:31,088 --> 00:39:33,928
could I ever forget today?

400
00:39:38,728 --> 00:39:40,608
Go on. Why wouldn’t you forget?

401
00:39:44,288 --> 00:39:45,488
Never mind.

402
00:39:45,488 --> 00:39:48,368
Tomorrow we’ll go back to our normal lives.

403
00:39:48,408 --> 00:39:50,728
You’ll go be a superstar leading actress,

404
00:39:50,728 --> 00:39:53,248
and I’ll go back to auditioning for extras.

405
00:39:56,048 --> 00:39:57,248
That’s it?

406
00:40:05,448 --> 00:40:06,728
That’s it.

407
00:40:07,928 --> 00:40:10,448
What about you?

408
00:40:10,968 --> 00:40:13,728
Don’t you have anything to say to me?

409
00:40:24,328 --> 00:40:25,448
No.

410
00:40:30,288 --> 00:40:31,568
Win.

411
00:40:31,568 --> 00:40:33,128
Wait for me.

412
00:41:04,368 --> 00:41:05,528
Win.

413
00:41:07,128 --> 00:41:09,048
I can put it away myself.

414
00:41:10,168 --> 00:41:11,928
But I’m happy to be of service.

415
00:41:12,808 --> 00:41:14,128
Are you flirting with me?

416
00:41:15,128 --> 00:41:16,328
At this point,

417
00:41:16,368 --> 00:41:18,048
I don’t even need to try.

418
00:41:18,088 --> 00:41:21,448
Win, what are you talking about?

419
00:41:24,048 --> 00:41:26,048
Are you blushing?

420
00:41:26,608 --> 00:41:28,448
That’s enough.

421
00:41:29,328 --> 00:41:31,848
You’re cute even when you blush.

422
00:41:37,488 --> 00:41:39,368
What are you laughing at?

423
00:41:39,368 --> 00:41:40,728
Let me see.

424
00:41:40,768 --> 00:41:42,128
No.

425
00:41:42,168 --> 00:41:43,808
So when a superstar sleeps,

426
00:41:43,848 --> 00:41:47,728
do they really leave
their mouth wide open like this?

427
00:41:48,088 --> 00:41:49,368
No.

428
00:41:50,208 --> 00:41:53,608
I’ve seen you on screen looking so pretty,
but when you sleep,

429
00:41:53,648 --> 00:41:55,408
you don’t even try to pose?

430
00:41:55,448 --> 00:41:58,608
You’re totally out cold
with your mouth wide open.

431
00:41:58,608 --> 00:42:01,008
You love teasing me. Give it here.

432
00:42:01,048 --> 00:42:02,608
- No.
- Give it here.

433
00:42:02,648 --> 00:42:03,928
- Give it here.
- I won’t.

434
00:42:04,408 --> 00:42:06,528
Delete it right now.

435
00:42:06,528 --> 00:42:08,728
No, I’m not deleting it.

436
00:42:08,768 --> 00:42:09,928
No.

437
00:42:09,968 --> 00:42:12,328
This is your luckiest moment ever.

438
00:42:12,368 --> 00:42:13,928
If you’re so sure, come and get it.

439
00:42:16,648 --> 00:42:17,848
Where are you going?

440
00:42:19,488 --> 00:42:20,488
No.

441
00:42:22,368 --> 00:42:23,368
No.

442
00:42:25,088 --> 00:42:26,208
Wanneung…

443
00:42:31,408 --> 00:42:33,048
I won’t give it to you.

444
00:42:33,048 --> 00:42:35,128
I won’t. I won’t.

445
00:42:35,168 --> 00:42:37,568
No matter what, I’m not giving it to you.

446
00:42:40,888 --> 00:42:42,848
Where did you go?

447
00:42:43,648 --> 00:42:45,528
- No, I won’t.
- Give it to me.

448
00:42:45,568 --> 00:42:48,448
- No.
- Are you going to hand it over nicely?

449
00:42:48,928 --> 00:42:51,048
If not, I’ll just sit on you like this.

450
00:42:51,208 --> 00:42:53,128
Even if you sit all day, I won’t give it to you.

451
00:44:03,608 --> 00:44:04,608
Tom.

452
00:44:06,608 --> 00:44:08,488
Several reporters contacted me.

453
00:44:08,528 --> 00:44:10,128
They said they couldn’t reach you.

454
00:44:10,608 --> 00:44:13,128
They want to interview you
about returning to films.

455
00:44:16,368 --> 00:44:17,848
Let’s hold off for now.

456
00:44:18,248 --> 00:44:19,728
I don’t want to be in the news yet.

457
00:44:21,008 --> 00:44:22,048
I know.

458
00:44:22,288 --> 00:44:23,928
So I turned them all down.

459
00:44:25,008 --> 00:44:26,008
Thank you.

460
00:44:32,848 --> 00:44:33,928
And...

461
00:44:34,088 --> 00:44:35,408
Are you going to visit May?

462
00:44:36,888 --> 00:44:38,248
What happened to her?

463
00:44:39,568 --> 00:44:40,768
You don’t know?

464
00:44:40,808 --> 00:44:42,248
It’s big news.

465
00:44:42,808 --> 00:44:45,368
She got into a car accident yesterday.

466
00:44:48,328 --> 00:44:49,728
How is she?

467
00:44:49,768 --> 00:44:51,048
She’s okay now.

468
00:44:51,768 --> 00:44:53,048
So, are you going?

469
00:45:14,568 --> 00:45:16,528
You can visit her for me.

470
00:45:17,528 --> 00:45:20,648
Anyway, thank you for today.

471
00:48:29,888 --> 00:48:30,928
Are you going to sleep already?

472
00:48:30,968 --> 00:48:32,528
You haven’t eaten yet.

473
00:48:33,288 --> 00:48:35,368
I’m sleepy.

474
00:48:35,408 --> 00:48:36,768
I’m going to bed.

475
00:48:36,808 --> 00:48:38,128
But last night you…

476
00:48:40,848 --> 00:48:42,288
I...

477
00:48:42,448 --> 00:48:43,648
What about me?

478
00:48:48,248 --> 00:48:50,488
Aren’t you hungry?

479
00:48:50,488 --> 00:48:52,768
Then go cook something yourself.

480
00:48:54,968 --> 00:48:56,528
You…

481
00:48:57,928 --> 00:48:59,888
I took you out,

482
00:48:59,928 --> 00:49:03,168
took photos for you,
and even made you coffee this morning.

483
00:49:03,168 --> 00:49:05,208
Don’t you think you should return the favor?

484
00:49:05,968 --> 00:49:07,528
Cook for me, please.

485
00:49:08,008 --> 00:49:10,928
Come on, come on. Let’s go.
I’ll take you.

486
00:49:11,128 --> 00:49:12,328
Let’s go, let’s go.

487
00:49:22,568 --> 00:49:24,928
Just have some noodles then.

488
00:49:26,648 --> 00:49:28,008
Alright.

489
00:49:28,488 --> 00:49:29,528
But…

490
00:49:30,168 --> 00:49:32,368
add an egg for me too.

491
00:49:37,888 --> 00:49:40,648
It’s late, and you still want to eat all that.

492
00:50:03,688 --> 00:50:05,128
Win…

493
00:50:05,208 --> 00:50:06,848
thank you so much.

494
00:50:06,888 --> 00:50:10,048
I never thought you’d surprise
other people like this too.

495
00:50:10,088 --> 00:50:12,928
I’ve been wishing that day
would come soon as well.

496
00:50:13,048 --> 00:50:15,408
But that day would mean nothing

497
00:50:15,448 --> 00:50:17,208
if you weren’t by my side.

498
00:50:17,728 --> 00:50:19,968
You’ll have to wait and see my success.

499
00:50:23,888 --> 00:50:27,328
So you’re just leaving me here
talking to the fridge alone?

500
00:51:00,528 --> 00:51:03,528
One day, imagine you’re bathing a baby.

501
00:51:03,568 --> 00:51:06,248
Tilt slightly to the side, turn a bit.

502
00:51:06,288 --> 00:51:08,688
Rub soap on the upper arm, rub the soap.

503
00:51:08,728 --> 00:51:11,768
The water is really cold.
It hits the back…so cold.

504
00:51:11,808 --> 00:51:14,728
Come in too, come in.
Just a little closer, a bit more.

505
00:51:15,008 --> 00:51:17,928
Stroke it, one day stroke it,
rub soap on the arm.

506
00:51:17,928 --> 00:51:19,768
Moss, you can record this scene.

507
00:51:19,808 --> 00:51:21,768
Okay, for this one I’ll go full singer mode.

508
00:51:21,768 --> 00:51:23,848
If we’re going to sleep, one day…

509
00:51:23,888 --> 00:51:25,968
hands clasped, resting on the pillow.

510
00:51:26,008 --> 00:51:27,688
Tilt your face forty-five degrees.

511
00:51:27,728 --> 00:51:29,648
Close your eyes.

512
00:51:29,688 --> 00:51:31,888
And give me a slight smile.

513
00:51:31,928 --> 00:51:34,368
Smile. I said smile.

514
00:51:34,408 --> 00:51:35,568
Have you ever smiled before?

515
00:51:35,608 --> 00:51:37,128
Smile.

516
00:51:38,648 --> 00:51:39,848
Alright.

517
00:51:39,888 --> 00:51:42,568
Move. I need movement.

518
00:51:42,608 --> 00:51:44,928
Slowly. Moss, keep rolling.

519
00:51:44,968 --> 00:51:46,408
That’s good.

520
00:51:46,448 --> 00:51:48,728
No, change, change, change.

521
00:51:48,728 --> 00:51:51,648
Hands like this. Down and up.

522
00:52:02,088 --> 00:52:03,328
Is that okay, Moss?

523
00:52:09,488 --> 00:52:10,648
Stop.

524
00:52:10,968 --> 00:52:12,208
That’s enough.

525
00:52:14,648 --> 00:52:15,728
Okay, kids.

526
00:52:36,248 --> 00:52:37,568
That’s really good.

527
00:52:39,208 --> 00:52:40,928
So sweet.

528
00:52:49,768 --> 00:52:50,848
Excellent.

529
00:52:51,408 --> 00:52:52,568
Break, everyone.

530
00:52:52,608 --> 00:52:54,808
Moss, get some water.
Bank, get some water.

531
00:52:55,528 --> 00:52:58,448
After wrap today,
I’m treating you all to som tam.

532
00:53:12,328 --> 00:53:15,088
Wanneung got the role in this movie, right?

533
00:53:16,288 --> 00:53:18,648
my dream is getting closer and closer.

534
00:53:18,648 --> 00:53:19,448
Khun Win.

535
00:53:19,448 --> 00:53:21,368
Can I sleep in your room?

536
00:53:38,910 --> 00:53:41,110
- Hey.
- Beautiful, right?

537
00:53:41,790 --> 00:53:44,710
So what do you think of this pose?

538
00:53:45,070 --> 00:53:46,710
Very mystical.

539
00:53:47,430 --> 00:53:48,430
Hey…

540
00:53:48,990 --> 00:53:51,030
Who taught you that pose?

541
00:53:51,750 --> 00:53:53,430
Doesn’t the photographer complain?

542
00:53:53,470 --> 00:53:55,190
I saw him smiling.

543
00:53:55,230 --> 00:53:58,710
He didn’t say anything.
I guess he liked it.

544
00:53:59,750 --> 00:54:01,070
Look…

545
00:54:01,110 --> 00:54:03,350
This pose right here.
He was grinning big.

546
00:54:03,870 --> 00:54:05,630
You only do weird poses.

547
00:54:05,670 --> 00:54:07,230
If you send this as your profile,

548
00:54:07,270 --> 00:54:09,550
you’ll probably get comedy roles for sure.

549
00:54:10,350 --> 00:54:12,790
Give it here. Why are you laughing?

550
00:54:12,830 --> 00:54:15,750
If you’re so good at it, then teach me.

551
00:54:16,550 --> 00:54:18,750
Please, teach me.

552
00:54:18,990 --> 00:54:20,150
Please?

553
00:54:26,230 --> 00:54:27,790
Where are you going?

554
00:54:34,550 --> 00:54:36,910
- Okay.
- Are you taking photos?

555
00:54:37,030 --> 00:54:39,310
- Yes.
- Then give me a second.

556
00:54:39,590 --> 00:54:42,310
- Let’s try one more round.
- Just a second.

557
00:54:43,590 --> 00:54:44,830
I’m ready.

558
00:54:45,030 --> 00:54:46,030
Come on.

559
00:54:48,990 --> 00:54:52,430
One, two, three.

560
00:54:56,630 --> 00:54:59,630
- Not that exaggerated.
- Okay.

561
00:54:59,670 --> 00:55:01,950
Let me find the angle first.

562
00:55:02,710 --> 00:55:04,550
Look beautiful.

563
00:55:04,550 --> 00:55:05,630
One…

564
00:55:09,270 --> 00:55:11,230
Maybe not so good. One second.

565
00:55:11,230 --> 00:55:15,950
Relax your body. Get up and jump first.
Jump, jump. Right now you look like a robot.

566
00:55:16,030 --> 00:55:17,030
Come on.

567
00:55:19,190 --> 00:55:20,630
Your hands shouldn’t be that stiff.

568
00:55:21,270 --> 00:55:22,630
Beautiful.

569
00:55:22,950 --> 00:55:24,070
Okay.

570
00:55:24,110 --> 00:55:25,830
Match your face with your hands.

571
00:55:31,390 --> 00:55:32,430
Like this.

572
00:55:33,430 --> 00:55:36,190
- Hey, wait a second…
- What’s wrong?

573
00:55:36,230 --> 00:55:38,150
I can’t hold it anymore. I really need to pee.

574
00:55:38,190 --> 00:55:39,630
Don’t go yet.

575
00:55:39,670 --> 00:55:40,830
It’s just getting…

576
00:55:41,390 --> 00:55:43,030
So good.

577
00:55:43,470 --> 00:55:45,470
(P’ Tong)

578
00:55:45,510 --> 00:55:46,550
(P’ Tong)

579
00:56:03,870 --> 00:56:04,950
Khun Win.

580
00:56:14,110 --> 00:56:15,430
Hello, P’ Tong.

581
00:56:15,430 --> 00:56:18,350
Win, I’m calling to confirm the movie.

582
00:56:18,750 --> 00:56:21,270
The producer will contact you.

583
00:56:21,270 --> 00:56:23,030
To check your workshop schedule.

584
00:56:24,230 --> 00:56:25,350
Okay.

585
00:56:25,510 --> 00:56:26,550
And…

586
00:56:26,710 --> 00:56:29,310
What about our agreement?

587
00:56:29,310 --> 00:56:30,710
Don’t worry.

588
00:56:31,030 --> 00:56:33,150
I’ve added more scenes for your kid.

589
00:56:38,910 --> 00:56:39,910
So that means...

590
00:56:40,390 --> 00:56:43,150
Wanneung got the role in this movie, right?

591
00:56:44,470 --> 00:56:46,910
At first there were some issues.

592
00:56:46,950 --> 00:56:51,030
But once they heard you guaranteed her,

593
00:56:51,390 --> 00:56:52,950
the investor agreed.

594
00:56:55,110 --> 00:56:56,910
Okay. Thank you.

595
00:57:10,310 --> 00:57:13,830
Wanneung, what’s wrong?

596
00:57:16,110 --> 00:57:17,230
Calm down.

597
00:57:17,270 --> 00:57:18,870
Khun Win…

598
00:57:18,910 --> 00:57:20,150
Tell me what’s wrong.

599
00:57:20,590 --> 00:57:21,590
Khun Win…

600
00:57:21,630 --> 00:57:23,670
P’ Waanwaan called to say I got the movie.

601
00:57:23,670 --> 00:57:27,310
And not just that…I’ll be in the same film as you.

602
00:57:29,390 --> 00:57:32,110
I’m so excited.

603
00:57:32,110 --> 00:57:34,150
The reason I got this role

604
00:57:34,190 --> 00:57:36,870
is because P’ Waanwaan pushed for me.

605
00:57:36,910 --> 00:57:40,430
Otherwise, I’d never have come this far.

606
00:57:42,270 --> 00:57:43,870
I’m in a movie.

607
00:57:47,790 --> 00:57:50,550
Aren’t you happy for me?

608
00:57:53,070 --> 00:57:54,550
Congratulations, Wanneung.

609
00:57:56,150 --> 00:57:57,550
Khun Win.

610
00:58:06,030 --> 00:58:07,630
I’m in a movie.

611
00:58:10,030 --> 00:58:13,230
Yay. Finally.

612
00:58:32,990 --> 00:58:34,430
Khun Win?

613
00:58:35,830 --> 00:58:36,950
Khun Win.

614
00:58:42,790 --> 00:58:45,750
Khun Win, I can’t sleep.

615
00:58:45,790 --> 00:58:46,870
What’s wrong?

616
00:58:46,950 --> 00:58:49,390
I’m still too excited.

617
00:58:49,470 --> 00:58:51,670
Can I sleep in your room?

618
00:58:53,190 --> 00:58:54,630
Please?

619
00:58:54,630 --> 00:58:55,710
Please.

620
01:00:17,510 --> 01:00:18,630
Khun Win.

621
01:00:22,470 --> 01:00:24,310
I’m really happy.

622
01:00:24,630 --> 01:00:27,790
So happy I can’t even put it into words.

623
01:00:28,630 --> 01:00:29,790
You know…

624
01:00:29,830 --> 01:00:32,670
my dream is getting closer and closer.

625
01:00:33,630 --> 01:00:36,270
And do you know what makes me happiest?

626
01:00:38,030 --> 01:00:39,230
What?

627
01:00:41,270 --> 01:00:45,070
You’re in that dream with me.

628
01:00:48,350 --> 01:00:49,510
Wanneung.

629
01:04:05,950 --> 01:04:07,870
We’re not running, no yoga.

630
01:04:07,990 --> 01:04:09,350
We’re going swimming.

631
01:04:09,390 --> 01:04:10,830
No, Win.

632
01:04:11,070 --> 01:04:12,070
Don’t.

633
01:04:12,590 --> 01:04:15,550
If one day Win still feels scared,
even knowing it’s risky,

634
01:04:15,590 --> 01:04:16,910
but still wants to try…

635
01:04:17,070 --> 01:04:19,870
that’s the day Win falls in love
with that person.

636
01:04:20,710 --> 01:04:23,830
A superstar like Win Pawee
dating a superstar like me

637
01:04:23,910 --> 01:04:27,110
is far more appropriate than
dating a supporting role like you.

638
01:04:27,150 --> 01:04:28,710
May and I aren’t anything anymore.

639
01:04:28,750 --> 01:04:30,230
- We broke up.
- You don’t have to explain.

640
01:04:30,230 --> 01:04:32,190
We’re not anything to each other.

641
01:04:32,230 --> 01:04:35,710
Wanneung and I are dating.

642
01:04:35,950 --> 01:04:38,270
Two, two.

643
01:04:39,310 --> 01:04:41,150
- Cut.
- You’ve got charm.

644
01:04:42,830 --> 01:04:45,670
Getting choke-held all the time.

645
01:04:46,230 --> 01:04:48,070
You’re enjoying it.

646
01:04:48,070 --> 01:04:49,790
- Yes.
- Raw chicken.

647
01:04:49,830 --> 01:04:51,590
Then don’t eat it raw.

648
01:04:53,150 --> 01:04:54,590
This is fun.

649
01:04:54,630 --> 01:04:57,750
- I was wondering if it would stand up.
- It can stand.

650
01:04:58,310 --> 01:05:00,190
Belle…

651
01:05:00,950 --> 01:05:03,150
Belle’s going to throw up.

652
01:05:03,510 --> 01:05:04,830
How do I get down?

653
01:05:04,830 --> 01:05:06,470
I’ll carry you.
